column5: Been a decent summer out here. Lots of trips with some big fish being boated. Not crazy numbers yet but they should be on soon. http://img.tapatalk.com/d/14/08/10/gu8yqypa.jpghttp://img.tapatalk.com/d/14/08/10/5eberega.jpghttp://img.tapatalk.com/d/14/08/10/ejybytu9.jpghttp://img.tapatalk.com/d/14/08/10/8yre3ypa.jpghttp://img.tapatalk.com/d/14/08/10/ruva2yre.jpghttp://img.tapatalk.com/d/14/08/10/8e6upuzy.jpghttp://img.tapatalk.com/d/14/08/10/ena8ave8.jpg

Great shots........Oswego harbor used to be a big walleye factory and still could be today if anyone ever put a few back in. Judging from the great daylight photos you got, I'd say you fished some of the offshore lumps where the big girls still hang out.
Yup offshore for sure. All of those were released. I have only kept one this summer and it's because it was hooked bad. What a fishery.
